scene.message:
Kuroori: Oh, {ctl0f:1}!{nl}
This is quite an{nl}
interesting incident.{waitkey}{clearbox}Could be the work of{nl}
aliens...!{wait_fr:32}{nl}
Heh heh heh...{waitkey}{clearbox}No really, this time{nl}
I mean it.{nl}
You can trust me!{waitkey}{ret}

{color:2}Kuroori Tsutomu.{nl}
Known as "Devil Boy."{nl}
Occult expert, though he's{nl}
often off the mark.{waitkey}{ret}

Kuroori: You know "The{nl}
Snow Queen," right?{nl}
The fairy tale?{waitkey}{clearbox}It's a traditional play{nl}
here at St. Hermelin...{nl}
Heh heh... just listen.{waitkey}{clearbox}In the play, the Snow{nl}
Queen always wears a mask.{nl}
Here's where it gets good.{waitkey}{clearbox}That mask is cursed.{nl}
Students who played the{nl}
Snow Queen kept dying.{waitkey}Interesting, right?{waitkey}{clearbox}But apparently one girl{nl}
escaped the curse{nl}
entirely.{waitkey}{clearbox}No one knows who she was.{nl}
If we found out,{nl}
it'd be a clue...{nl}
Heh heh heh...{waitkey}{ret}

Student: Hey, you!{nl}
I know you know something.{nl}
Please, help me out!{waitkey}{ret}

Student: Don't push people{nl}
too hard — who knows{nl}
what they'll do!{waitkey}Probably true for{nl}
demons too.{waitkey}{ret}
